09:56.697 --> 09:59.197
Megan, Megan, Megan, Megan.

10:01.946 --> 10:03.279
Megan.

10:05.906 --> 10:07.405
Fucking Jackie.

10:09.209 --> 10:11.176
[panting]

10:11.211 --> 10:13.211
[instrumental music]

10:27.928 --> 10:29.928
[panting]

10:50.250 --> 10:53.251
[intense music]

10:58.427 --> 10:59.860
Hey!

11:02.263 --> 11:03.930
You wanna take it out?

11:11.566 --> 11:12.665
What do you want?

11:13.661 --> 11:14.993
<i>Whoever you are.</i>

11:21.718 --> 11:23.050
<i>Please.</i>

11:25.367 --> 11:26.866
I never liked the name.

11:30.471 --> 11:31.804
It never felt like me.

11:33.541 --> 11:35.789
<i>And when I figured out
who I was..</i>

11:36.096 --> 11:37.796
<i>That I was gay..</i>

11:41.896 --> 11:43.406
...I changed it.

11:45.244 --> 11:47.244
<i>I should've mentioned it
to you before.</i>

11:48.685 --> 11:50.374
<i>I'm sorry, Jules.</i>

11:50.994 --> 11:52.994
That's not who I am anymore.

12:02.659 --> 12:03.991
Close your eyes.

12:05.851 --> 12:07.016
Please.

12:07.356 --> 12:08.588
Please.

12:13.200 --> 12:14.365
[exhales]

12:27.951 --> 12:30.051
Okay, open it.

12:40.554 --> 12:41.820
<i>Do you like it?</i>

12:45.532 --> 12:47.532
<i>God, you're so cheesy.</i>

12:48.168 --> 12:50.068
[laughing]

12:50.103 --> 12:51.703
<i>I'm still pissed at you.</i>

12:52.034 --> 12:53.172
<i>I am.</i>

12:56.777 --> 12:58.209
[gunshot]

13:05.986 --> 13:07.252
[gunshot]

13:08.907 --> 13:10.674
The scope isn't aligned alright.

13:12.492 --> 13:14.726
I still can't believe your dad
never took you hunting.

13:16.453 --> 13:18.730
Target practice
is enough for me.

13:18.819 --> 13:21.320
Killing for sport
isn't exactly my thing.

13:24.200 --> 13:26.533
Killing for sport
is not what hunting is.

13:27.405 --> 13:28.805
[cocks gun]

13:28.949 --> 13:30.315
Trust me.

13:33.286 --> 13:34.685
Straighten your shoulders, babe.

13:35.382 --> 13:36.948
Your form is all wrong.

13:36.983 --> 13:38.983
[gunshots]

13:44.803 --> 13:46.002
Holy shit!

13:46.960 --> 13:48.493
I know.

13:50.288 --> 13:53.689
My dad, he used to hunt
every summer up here.

13:55.769 --> 13:57.101
One summer..

13:58.805 --> 14:00.939
...he wakes me
and my friend Jenny up

14:00.974 --> 14:03.441
at the crack of dawn,
and he says to us

14:04.878 --> 14:07.445
"It's time you girls learn
a bit about life."

14:08.582 --> 14:09.418
[chuckling]

14:09.454 --> 14:10.454
So...

14:10.917 --> 14:14.719
...he hands each of us a rifle

14:14.930 --> 14:16.422
and off we go.

14:17.157 --> 14:21.193
We're crying
and complaining and..

14:21.533 --> 14:25.414
And he's giving us hell
for being such girls.

14:25.665 --> 14:26.965
Sounds like it.

14:27.078 --> 14:29.211
[chuckles]

14:29.369 --> 14:31.970
And eventually I go
wondering off on my own

14:33.106 --> 14:34.639
but I get turned around.

14:36.810 --> 14:38.510
The next thing I know..

14:38.545 --> 14:40.512
I find myself face to face

14:40.547 --> 14:43.982
with this massive black bear.

14:46.445 --> 14:47.853
It's just standing there.

14:48.133 --> 14:49.863
Not more than 20 feet
away from me

14:49.899 --> 14:52.047
<i>and it's looking right at me.</i>

14:52.938 --> 14:54.898
So I line her up in my sights..

14:55.453 --> 14:57.286
Boom! Down she goes.

14:58.465 --> 15:00.031
<i>I race up to it thinking</i>

15:00.567 --> 15:03.234
how proud he's gonna be,
it's my first kill.

15:07.577 --> 15:09.376
But she's still breathing.

15:11.378 --> 15:13.177
She's struggling.

15:16.126 --> 15:19.805
Trying to stand up
and... screaming out.

15:25.581 --> 15:27.147
What did you do?

15:28.904 --> 15:31.471
I lined my gun up
to do the humane thing.

15:34.432 --> 15:35.931
But it jammed.

15:37.136 --> 15:40.671
<i>So I just... stood over it..</i>

15:42.270 --> 15:44.270
...the next 20 minutes and I..

15:45.595 --> 15:49.330
I watched the life
slowly fade from her eyes.

15:51.751 --> 15:53.251
<i>I'll never forget it.</i>

16:01.225 --> 16:03.274
My dad gave this to me
afterwards.

16:12.092 --> 16:14.459
Just in case my gun ever
jammed again.

16:18.031 --> 16:20.023
He used to say to me..

16:20.447 --> 16:24.048
"You only kill
what keeps you alive."

16:28.118 --> 16:29.961
What does that mean?

16:30.367 --> 16:33.058
It means we ate
every single square inch of meat

16:33.093 --> 16:35.093
off that bear over
the next month.

16:37.307 --> 16:39.107
Nothing went to waste.

16:46.632 --> 16:49.033
That's a pretty fucked up story.

16:49.185 --> 16:51.118
[Jackie laughs]
Yeah, I know.

16:51.945 --> 16:54.913
[insects chirping]

16:54.948 --> 16:57.949
[intense music]

17:00.820 --> 17:02.820
[birds chirping]

17:14.931 --> 17:16.998
<i>Hey, babe!
I couldn't find a pen</i>

17:17.108 --> 17:18.502
<i>so I'm leaving a voice mail.</i>

17:18.538 --> 17:21.006
<i>I know, it's so '90s, right?</i>

17:21.040 --> 17:24.175
<i>Listen, I'm heading into town
for a bit to grab a few things</i>

17:24.210 --> 17:25.977
<i>but, uh, I'll be back
in the afternoon.</i>

17:26.012 --> 17:31.282
<i>P.S. You looked really cute
sleeping this morning. I love..</i>

